Opportunity to immediately owner occupy in the heart of Leichhardt. Norton Street offers some of the streets best retail and dining experiences.
54 Norton Street is 268sqm also features some development potential; this single story building is surrounded by primarily two level mixed use retail/residential buildings - the B2 Local Centre zoning has not been utilized to its full potential.

The property is a single story building, located within the main business centre of Leichhardt, Norton Street. With an existing fit out for a restaurant, cafA© or bar. The entrance of the property features timber flooring, two outdoor dining spaces, and two large dining rooms, one which can be dedicated as a private function room and bar.
The property is currently vacant; fit out for a restaurant or cafe - ideal for an owner occupier looking to set up in the main street in Leichhardt, or an investor seeking a value add opportunity.

The property was returning $119,000 p.a + GST 12 months ago with an active tenant. At 268sqm, that equates to $444/sqm.

A TROPHY SYDNEY-METRO NEIGHBOURHOOD SHOPPING CENTRE

CBRE is pleased to offer for sale Norton Plaza and Norton Central, a trophy metropolitan neighbourhood shopping centre located just 6.5km from Sydney’s CBD.

The properties are the jewel in the crown of Leichhardt, Norton Street’s thriving retail precinct and the Inner West. The centre boasts unmatched fundamentals that are the epitome of non-discretionary convenience based retailing.

A number of key investment highlights are outlined below:

- Anchored by strong performing Coles (trading 36% above the benchmark) & Harris Farm Supermarkets
- Unmatched flexibility over two titles, on 12,014sqm of inner Sydney freehold land
- Convenient design over 11,751sqm of combined GLA and 364 car parks 
- Highly affluent catchment, with per capita income levels 45% above the Sydney metro average
- Total Trade area expenditure forecast to grow by over $2 billion by 2031
- Ranked as one of the best performing shopping centres in Australia^
- Fully leased net income $8,701,000 pa


For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact the exclusive sales and marketing agents 

*All figures are approximate only
^ Top 20 Mini Guns, Shopping Centres Australia

CBRE, as exclusive selling agents, are delighted to present for the first time in over 40 years, 146 Norton Street, Leichhardt.

This property is a two-storey mixed use building in the heart of Leichhardt’s retail village. Commanding a high profile location along the one of the busiest streets in Leichhardt, the property affords exceptional vehicular and foot traffic exposure. This exposure is strengthened by the property’s 5m* frontage to Norton Street, providing great signage opportunities. The property is conveniently located within close proximity to surrounding suburbs, cafes and public transport. 

146 Norton Street comprises a total area of 205sqm* over three levels and is food ready, with the inclusion of a grease trap and seating permitted outside on Norton Street (STCA). The property also benefits from four car spaces, male and female amenities and basement storage.

An exciting opportunity is presented with 146 Norton Street, with the property being suitable for multiple uses (STCA). An investor is able to rent out the whole building for circa $75,000* per annum or rent out the second level as a separate tenancy. 

146 Norton Street benefits from the following key attributes:
- 205sqm* over three levels plus 4 car spaces
- Amenities and grease trap provided
- High profile location
- Proximity to local amenities and public transport

Please contact agent for further details.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
